Explanation

A font is defined by three things:
	a weight (regular or bold, etc.),
	a style (roman or italic, etc.),
	a form (upperscripts, small caps, etc.).

But softwares (both troff and fonts), and after them end
users, don't make real difference between weight, styles and
forms. So, we have to create the difference, and give a
simple and usual interface to these well defined fonts.

That's why we use three letter to name fonts, and mount fonts
using these names. To access a font, strings definition
are shortcuts to these names.

First letter define the weight, second one the style, and
third one the form.

weight:
	R regular
	K book
	B bold
	E extra
style:
	R roman
	I italic
forms:
	N normal
	C small caps
	A acronyms
	U superscript (upper)
	F final glyphs
	M monospace

Thus, RRN means regular roman with normal form, which is
usually named "roman"; and BIU means bold italic
superscript, etc.


When using a font, we usually need: a default weight, an
emboldened weight. For each of these, we need a default
style, and an emphasis style (italic). For each of these, we
need a normal form, small caps, acronyms, superscripts, and
special glyphs.

So, end user names of fonts are:
R RC RA RU RF		default weight, default style
B BC BA BU BF		emboldened, default style
I IC IA IU IF		default weight, emphasis style
BI BIC BIA BIU BIF	emboldened, emphasis style

We link these names to real fonts using strings, with:
weight0	= default weight
weight1 = emboldened weight
style0  = default style
style1  = emphasis style

So, R is a shortcut to [weight0][style0]N,
BIA is a shortcut to [weight1][style1]A,
and IC is a shortcut to [weight0][style1]C.

To embolden a whole set of font, we use some macros.

..
.nr data-u-libertine 1
.\"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
.\" Strings
.\" (Use \E to define a "\" which is not interpreted
.\" in copy mode, to may use fonts as macro argument)
.de font:strings
.	\" normal form
.	ds P \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style0]N]
.	ds R \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style0]N]
.	ds B \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style0]N]
.	ds I \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style1]N]
.	ds BI \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style1]N]
.	\" small caps form
.	ds C \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style0]C]
.	ds BC \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style0]C]
.	ds BIC \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style1]C]
.	ds IC \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style1]C]
.	\" acronyms
.	ds A \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style0]C]
.	ds BA \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style0]C]
.	ds BIA \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style1]C]
.	ds IA \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style1]C]
.	\" superscript
.	ds U \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style0]U]
.	ds BU \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style0]U]
.	ds BIU \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style1]U]
.	ds IU \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style1]U]
.	\" Final glyphs
.	\" Since there's no final glyphs, map to N
.	ds F \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style0]N]
.	ds BF \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style0]N]
.	ds BIF \f[\\E*[font-weight1]\\E*[font-style1]N]
.	ds IF \f[\\E*[font-weight0]\\E*[font-style1]N]
.	\" usefull shortcuts
.	ds { \f[RRU]
.	ds } \f[RRN]
.	\"ds siecle \\fA\\$1\\fP\\fUe\\fP
..
.\" ornament uniE002
.ds font-orn \[uniE002]
.\"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
.\"	Macros to change weight
.de font:text
.	\" default font
.	\" regular, bold, roman, italic
.	ds font-weight0 R
.	ds font-weight1 B
.	ds font-style0 R
.	ds font-style1 I
.	font:strings
.	ft RRN
.	lang:char
..
.de font:note
.	\" font for small text
.	\" book, extra, roman, italic
.	ds font-weight0 R
.	ds font-weight1 B
.	ds font-style0 R
.	ds font-style1 I
.	font:strings
.	ft RRN
.	lang:char
..
.de font:note-it
.	\" small text, reverse italic
.	\" book, extra, italic, roman
.	ds font-weight0 R
.	ds font-weight1 B
.	ds font-style0 I
.	ds font-style1 R
.	font:strings
.	ft RIN
.	lang:char
..
.de font:head
.	\" decoration for headers
.	\" extra, extrabold, italic, roman
.	ds font-weight0 B
.	ds font-weight1 B
.	ds font-style0 I
.	ds font-style1 R
.	font:strings
.	ft BIN
.	lang:char
..
.de font:subhead
.	\" decoration for subheads
.	\" bold, extra, italic, roman
.	ds font-weight0 B
.	ds font-weight1 B
.	ds font-style0 I
.	ds font-style1 R
.	font:strings
.	ft BIN
.	lang:char
..
.de font:endhead
.	\" reset after headers
.	font:text
..
.de font:code
.	\" TODO: use monospace font
.	ds P \f[RRM]
.	ds R \f[RRM]
.	ds B \f[BRM]
.	ds I \f[RIM]
.	ds BI \f[BIM]
.	\" small caps form
.	ds C \f[RRM]
.	ds BC \f[BRM]
.	ds BIC \f[BIM]
.	\" acronyms
.	ds A \f[RRM]
.	ds BA \f[BRM]
.	ds BIA \f[BIM]
.	\" superscript
.	ds U \f[RRM]
.	ds BU \f[BRM]
.	ds BIU \f[BIM]
.	\" Final glyphs
.	\" Since there's no final glyphs, map to N
.	ds F \f[RRM]
.	ds BF \f[BRM]
.	ds BIF \f[BIM]
.	\" usefull shortcuts
.	ds { \f[RRM]
.	ds } \f[RRM]
.	ft RRM
.	lang:rchar \" remove no-break spaces
..
.\"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
.\" Make ligatures
.de font:liga
.	flig \\$1 ct \[c_t] st \[s_t] \"sp \[s_p]
.	flig \\$1 fb \[f_b] \"ffb \[f_f_b]
.	flig \\$1 ff \[f_f] fh \[f_h] ffh \[f_f_h]
.	flig \\$1 fi \[fi] ffi \[f_f_i]
.	flig \\$1 fj \[f_j] ffj \[f_f_j] fk \[f_k]
.	flig \\$1 ffk \[f_f_k] fl \[fl]
.	flig \\$1 ffl \[f_f_l] ft \[f_t] fft \[f_f_t] Th \[T_h]
.	flig \\$1 ck \[c_k] ch \[c_h] tt \[t_t]
.	\"char \[doublepoint] ..
.	\"flig \\$1 .. \[doublepoint] ... \[ellipsis]
..
.de font:noliga
.	fdeferlig \\$1 ff ffi ffl fl fi
..
.\""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
.\" Mount fonts for text
.\""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
.\"	fp 1 R ApollinePTF-Regular otf
.\"	fp 2 B ApollinePTF-ExtraBold otf
.\"	fp 3 I ApollinePTF-Italic otf
.\"	fp 4 BI ApollinePTF-ExtraBoldItalic otf
.de font:mount
.	\" $1: weight and style symbols
.	\" $2: name of font
.	\" N: default form
.	fp \\nz \\$1N \\$2 otf
.	\"font:liga \\$1N
.	\" C: small caps
.	fp \\n+z \\$1C \\$2 otf
.	feature \\$1C +smcp +lnum
.	font:noliga \\$1C
.	\" A: acronyms
.	\"fp \\n+z \\$1A \\$2 otf
.	\"feature \\$1A +smcp +lnum +c2sc 
.	\"font:noliga \\$1A
.	\" U: superscripts
.	fp \\n+z \\$1U \\$2 otf
.	feature \\$1U +sups
.	font:noliga \\$1U
.	\" No final glyphs in LinLibertine
.	nr z +1
..
.\"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
.\" mount all fonts
.\" TODO: find a way to mount on demand
.nr z 11 1 \" position 9 and 10 are reserved
.font:mount RR LinLibertine_R
.font:liga RRN
.font:mount RI LinLibertine_RI
.font:liga RIN
.\"font:mount KR LinLibertine_RZ
.\"font:mount KI LinLibertine_RZI
.font:mount BR LinLibertine_RB
.font:mount BI LinLibertine_RBI
.\" No extra font on LinLibertine
.\" Monospace font
.fp \nz RRM LinBiolinum_R otf
.font:noliga RRM
.fp \n+z RIM LinBiolinum_RI otf
.font:noliga RIM
.fp \n+z BRM LinBiolinum_RB otf
.font:noliga BRM
.fp \n+z BIM LinBiolinum_RB otf
.rm z
.\"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
.\" Opentype features
.ig

Letters
-------
aalt 	Access All Alternates
smcp	Small Capitals
c2sc	Capitals to Small Caps
		used to type acronyms)
case	Case-Sensitive Forms
		Punctuation marks for all-capitals sequences
		Lining figures are prefered than oldstyle figures
swsh	Swash
		all swash glyphs and end glyphs
fina	Terminal Forms
		Alternate forms for the end of a word
salt	Stylistic Alternates
		a, A, รง, ร alternates
ordn	Ordinals
		Letter superscript to use after figures
sups	superscript
		letters and figure superscripts

Figures
-------
onum	Oldstyle Figures (default)
		Fit better in normal text
		Override lnum
lnum	Lining Figures
		Figures that looks better in all capital forms
		Override onum
pnum	Proportional Figures
		proportionnal inter-glyph space
		Override tnum (tabular figures)
tnum	Tabular figures
		figures in uniform (tabular, monospace) interglyph space
		Override pnum
frac	Fractions
		replace figures by Numr, and slash by fraction
		Should be followed by dnom
numr	Numerators
		Used before a slash in a fraction
dnom	Denominator
		For figures which follow a slash in a fraction
sinf	Scientific Inferiors
		smaller figures glyphs which sit lower than the standard baseline
		for chemical or mathematical notation

Ornaments and stylistic sets
----------------------------
ornm	Ornaments
		a->z A->K 0->9 punctuation
		orn.001 -> orn.039, etc.
ss01	Stylistic set 1
ss02	Stylistic set 2
ss03	Stylistic Set 3
ss05	Stylistic Set 5
ss06	Stylistic Set 6

Ligatures
